<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America and Merrill Lynch&#39;s Global Corporate and Investment Banking Asia Pacific business executes a client-led Corporate Banking strategy that has resulted in a highly profitable platform with sustainable revenue streams in excess of US$1 billion.  The group serves as a trusted advisor to premier corporate, institutional and government clients, helping them develop their strategic objectives and meet their financial needs by providing advice, financing, and services to a wide range of clients worldwide.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Placement</H3>
<p class="bac">
Analysts are hired and placed directly with a specific group.  Group placement is determined by considering business needs and the interests/skills of the Analyst.  The groups span across country, industry and product (not all groups exist in all countries):
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Country
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Australia</li>
			<li>Hong Kong</li>
			<li>India</li>
			<li>Japan</li>
			<li>Singapore</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Industry
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Consumer and Retail</li>
			<li>Energy and Power</li>
			<li>Financial Institutions</li>
			<li>Healthcare</li>
			<li>Industrials</li>
			<li>Real Estate</li> 
			<li>Resources</li>
			<li>Telecom, Media and Technology</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Product
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Financial Sponsors</li>
			<li>General Execution</li>
			<li>Mergers and Acquisitions</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<br>
<H3 class="bac">Responsibilities</H3>
<p class="bac">
Investment Banking Analysts play a key role in the origination and execution of work with key clients and typically take on many responsibilities, including but not limited to:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Working on deal teams with senior bankers and experts from other areas within the firm </li>
	<li>Conducting sophisticated financial analysis and relevant industry research </li>
	<li>Participating in due diligence sessions </li>
	<li>Assisting with structuring transactions, pricing and distributing securities, and closing deals </li>
	<li>Preparing and participating in client presentations, and marketing new products </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Education</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Final year undergraduate/master student, graduating in 2010</li>
	<li>On track to receive a minimum GPA 3.5/4 or  minimum 2:1 degree (UK system)</li>
	<li>Outstanding academic achievement </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Experience</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A track record of superior performance in extracurricular and professional activities </li>
	<li>Prior relevant internship experience advantageous</li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Skills and abilities </H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong quantitative and analytical skills 
	<li>Knowledge of accounting and finance, and strong interest in company financing </li>
	<li>Ability to apply advanced oral and written communication skills to create a positive impression and professional rapport </li>
	<li>Ability to work independently while functioning as part of a team </li>
	<li>Appropriate language capabilities </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Personal traits</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>High degree of professionalism and integrity</li>
	<li>A high degree of initiative and motivation </li>
	<li>Strong attention to detail </li>
	<li>Quick learner and interest in taking on new responsibilities</li>
	<li>Client focused </li>
	<li>Results oriented</li>
	<li>Ability to work well with others</li>
	<li>Ability to maintain composure and confidence while juggling conflicting priorities </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Full-time Analysts are hired upon completion of their undergraduate/master&#39;s degree.  Your career as an Analyst will begin with a formal training program which takes place in New York for all Analysts globally, and is considered one of the best in the industry.  Instruction is provided by Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America professionals and leading business school professors.
</p>
<p class="bac">
The training program includes:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A firm wide orientation program to introduce you to Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America</li>
	<li>An overview of the financial markets and essential business skills</li>
	<li>An intensive training program customized for Analysts that prepares you for your placement in Investment Banking by simulating actual work assignments, covering quantitative fundamentals, and preparing you for life as an Analyst</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
After the formal training program, Analysts relocate to the Asia Pacific office that hired them and begin working.  Training continues on the job and through the online learning network for continuing education as well as relevant classroom training throughout your career.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Graduates who join the offices in Australia and Japan will being in January and April respectively, and work for the months prior to attending training in New York which typically takes place in July.
</p>

